 Residents from the area, frantically contacted www.mobserver.co.za in the fear that the billowing column of smoke would spread through the neighbourhood. Upon the arrival of the journalists, the fire brigade was present and everything was under control. The homeowners confirmed that the blaze had been extinguished and that no injuries were sustained. They stated that their garage and servant quarters had caught alight but the rest of the home remains intact.      Middelburg police officer arrested during Hawks operation Botshabelo’s last song Five busted for dagga Nabbed cops granted bail  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za